.\" Manpage for pssst.
.\" Contact hello@pssst.name to correct errors or typos.
.TH man 1 "November 2015" "Pssst" "Pssst Manual"
.SH NAME
pssst \- Pssst CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
pssst [option|command] [username:password] [receiver message...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Pssst is a simple and secure way to exchange information.
.SH OPTIONS
.IP "-s --shell"
Run as interactive shell
.IP "-h --help"
Show usage informations
.IP "-l --license"
Show license
.IP "-v --version"
Show version
.SH COMMANDS
.B create
.RS
Creates an user or a box.
.RE
.B delete
.RS
Deletes an user or a box.
.RE
.B list
.RS
Lists all boxes.
.RE
.B pull
.RS
Pulls a message.
.RE
.B push
.RS
Pushes a message.
.RE
.SH FILES
.I ~/.pssst
.RS
Configuration file. See
.I README.md
for further details.
.RE
.I ~/.pssst.<user>
.RS
User specific data including private and public keys.
.RE
.SH AUTHORS
Christian & Christian <hello@pssst.name>
